---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Course Creators"
  description="Build advanced, content-rich open-source courses using course.yaml plus the OpenCourses content blueprint."
  chapterId="creators"
>
  <nav slot="toc">
    <a href="#downloads"      class="docs-toc-link">Download Templates</a>
    <a href="#layout"         class="docs-toc-link">Directory Layout</a>
    <a href="#overview"       class="docs-toc-link">Schema Overview</a>
    <a href="#s1-metadata"    class="docs-toc-link">§1 Metadata</a>
    <a href="#s2-identity"    class="docs-toc-link">§2 Identity</a>
    <a href="#s3-classify"    class="docs-toc-link">§3 Classification</a>
    <a href="#s4-effort"      class="docs-toc-link">§4 Effort</a>
    <a href="#s5-people"      class="docs-toc-link">§5 People</a>
    <a href="#s6-credits"     class="docs-toc-link">§6 Credits</a>
    <a href="#s7-prereqs"     class="docs-toc-link">§7 Prerequisites</a>
    <a href="#s8-outcomes"    class="docs-toc-link">§8 Outcomes</a>
    <a href="#content-blueprint" class="docs-toc-link">Content Blueprint</a>
    <a href="#s9-curriculum"  class="docs-toc-link">§9 Curriculum</a>
    <a href="#lesson-types"   class="docs-toc-link">Lesson Types</a>
    <a href="#s10-tests"      class="docs-toc-link">§10 Chapter Tests</a>
    <a href="#s11-assign"     class="docs-toc-link">§11 Assignments</a>
    <a href="#s12-final-test" class="docs-toc-link">§12 Final Test</a>
    <a href="#s13-final-proj" class="docs-toc-link">§13 Final Project</a>
    <a href="#s14-cert"       class="docs-toc-link">§14 Certificate</a>
    <a href="#s15-assets"     class="docs-toc-link">§15 Assets</a>
    <a href="#s16-triggers"   class="docs-toc-link">§16 Triggers</a>
    <a href="#s17-discussion" class="docs-toc-link">§17 Discussion</a>
    <a href="#s18-changelog"  class="docs-toc-link">§18 Changelog</a>
    <a href="#solutions"      class="docs-toc-link">solutions.yaml</a>
    <a href="#questions"      class="docs-toc-link">Question Types</a>
    <a href="#pr-workflow"    class="docs-toc-link">PR Workflow</a>
    <a href="#checklist"      class="docs-toc-link">Checklist</a>
  </nav>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ DOWNLOADS ═ -->
  <section id="downloads" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">
      Download Templates
      <span class="docs-section-badge" style="background:color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 12%,transparent);color:#a78bfa;border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 30%,transparent)">Start here</span>
    </h2>
    <p>Three files guide every course. Download the blueprint first, then fill the YAML files:</p>
    <div class="dl-grid">
      <a href={`${base}/templates/course-blueprint.md`} download="course-blueprint.md" class="dl-card">
        <div class="dl-card__icon">🧭</div>
        <div class="dl-card__body">
          <div class="dl-card__title">course-blueprint.md</div>
          <div class="dl-card__sub">Content design standard · Open-source-first</div>
          <div class="dl-card__desc">Mission, course flow, chapter quality bar, testing philosophy, open-source resource strategy, capstone expectations, and contribution path.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-card__btn">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="3" x2="12" y2="15"/></svg>
          Download
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/templates/course.yaml`} download="course.yaml" class="dl-card">
        <div class="dl-card__icon">📄</div>
        <div class="dl-card__body">
          <div class="dl-card__title">course.yaml</div>
          <div class="dl-card__sub">Schema v3.0 · 1644-line annotated template</div>
          <div class="dl-card__desc">Single source of truth. Contains the 18 engine sections plus <code>content_blueprint</code> for advanced open-source course quality.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-card__btn">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="3" x2="12" y2="15"/></svg>
          Download
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href={`${base}/templates/solutions.yaml`} download="solutions.yaml" class="dl-card">
        <div class="dl-card__icon">✓</div>
        <div class="dl-card__body">
          <div class="dl-card__title">solutions.yaml</div>
          <div class="dl-card__sub">Schema v3.0 · Companion answers and rubrics</div>
          <div class="dl-card__desc">All answers, grading rubrics, and sample solutions for every question in course.yaml. Commit it with the course so grading is transparent.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-card__btn">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><polyline points="7 10 12 15 17 10"/><line x1="12" y1="3" x2="12" y2="15"/></svg>
          Download
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--tip">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">✓</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">
        <strong>solutions.yaml is public by design.</strong> OpenCourses favors transparent grading and trusts learners to use published solutions for review rather than cheating.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ LAYOUT ═ -->
  <section id="layout" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Course Directory Layout</h2>
    <p>Every course lives under <code>engine/courses/&#123;slug&#125;/</code>. Copy the template directory to start:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">bash</span></div>
      <code>cp -r engine/courses/template engine/courses/your-slug
# then edit engine/courses/your-slug/course.yaml</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">tree</span></div>
      <code>engine/courses/your-slug/
├── course.yaml              ← edit this — single source of truth
├── solutions.yaml           ← public answers, rubrics, and grading config
├── course.json              ← auto-generated by parse-course on publish
├── course-detail.json       ← auto-generated player data (full lesson content)
├── contributors.json        ← auto-generated by detect-contributors
└── assets/
    ├── images/
    │   └── diagrams/        lesson diagrams and screenshots
    ├── code/                runnable code examples, by chapter
    │   └── ch-01/
    │       └── example.py
    ├── docs/                PDFs, cheatsheets, slide decks
    │   ├── ch-01-notes.pdf
    │   └── reference-card.pdf
    ├── data/                datasets for exercises
    ├── starter/             scaffolded projects, TODOs, local setup
    ├── tests/               generators, fuzz/property tests, benchmarks
    └── slides/              slide presentations</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ OVERVIEW ══ -->
  <section id="overview" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Schema Overview — 18 Engine Sections + Content Blueprint</h2>
    <p><code>course.yaml</code> follows schema v3.0. The 18 engine sections drive automation; <code>content_blueprint</code> strengthens course content quality and is parsed for authoring warnings.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Section</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Required</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>01</code></td><td><code>metadata</code></td><td>ID, version, status, visibility, dates, language</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>02</code></td><td><code>identity</code></td><td>Title, tagline, description, optional accent colors</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>03</code></td><td><code>classification</code></td><td>Category, tags, topics, level, audience, skills gained</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>04</code></td><td><code>effort</code></td><td>Hours breakdown, pace, completion weeks</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>05</code></td><td><code>people</code></td><td>Curator, contributors, reviewers</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>06</code></td><td><code>credits</code></td><td>Attribution for every external resource used</td><td>Yes if using external content</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>07</code></td><td><code>prerequisites</code></td><td>Knowledge, other courses, tools, accounts</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>08</code></td><td><code>outcomes</code></td><td>What students learn (by completion, by chapter)</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--</code></td><td><code>content_blueprint</code></td><td>Open-source-first content quality plan: flow, resource strategy, testing, capstone, contribution path</td><td>Recommended</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>09</code></td><td><code>curriculum</code></td><td>All chapters → sections → subsections → lessons</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>10</code></td><td><code>chapter_tests</code></td><td>Graded assessments gating chapter progression</td><td>Yes (one per chapter)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>11</code></td><td><code>chapter_assignments</code></td><td>Hands-on chapter projects submitted via GitHub</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>12</code></td><td><code>final_test</code></td><td>Comprehensive final assessment</td><td>Recommended</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>13</code></td><td><code>final_assignment</code></td><td>Capstone project</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>14</code></td><td><code>certificate</code></td><td>Completion certificate config and requirements</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>15</code></td><td><code>assets</code></td><td>File manifests (images, code, docs, data, slides)</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>16</code></td><td><code>triggers</code></td><td>GitHub Actions to fire on course lifecycle events</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>17</code></td><td><code>discussion</code></td><td>GitHub Discussions integration per-chapter or per-course</td><td>No</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>18</code></td><td><code>changelog</code></td><td>Version history — required before status: review</td><td>Yes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--info">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">ℹ️</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Fields marked <code>[REQUIRED]</code> inside the template must be filled before setting <code>metadata.status: review</code>. Fields marked <code>[OPTIONAL]</code> may be removed entirely if not needed. The YAML parser validates this at PR time.</div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section id="content-blueprint" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">
      Content Blueprint
      <span class="docs-section-badge" style="background:color-mix(in srgb,#2DD4BF 12%,transparent);color:#2DD4BF;border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,#2DD4BF 30%,transparent)">Recommended</span>
    </h2>
    <p>The OpenCourses blueprint is for course content quality, not a replacement folder structure. Keep using <code>course.yaml</code>; fill <code>content_blueprint</code> to show how the course becomes advanced, content-rich, reproducible, and open-source-first.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>content_blueprint:
  principles:
    - Uses open-source tooling whenever possible
    - References open-source implementations
    - Teaches through real repositories
    - Uses transparent evaluation systems
  flow:
    - foundations
    - environment-setup
    - guided-fundamentals
    - incremental-challenges
    - production-engineering
    - open-source-exploration
    - capstone-project
    - contribution-path
  resource_strategy:
    repositories:
      - https://github.com/org/repo
    open_books:
      - Book title or URL
    papers:
      - Paper title or URL
    rfcs_and_specs:
      - RFC/spec title or URL
  testing:
    types: [deterministic, randomized, fuzz, property-based, benchmark]
    generators:
      - assets/tests/fuzz-gen.py
  capstone:
    level: advanced
    type: scalable service
    requirements: [Production-ready, Deployable, Documented, Tested, Secure]
  contribution_path:
    - Open issues
    - Submit PRs
    - Improve documentation</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--info">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">ℹ️</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">The parser accepts <code>content_blueprint</code> and <code>parse-course.ts</code> warns when important content-design pieces are missing. This keeps the YAML structure stable while raising the quality bar for new courses.</div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 1: METADATA -->
  <section id="s1-metadata" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">
      §1 — Metadata
      <span class="docs-section-badge" style="background:color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 12%,transparent);color:#a78bfa;border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 30%,transparent)">Required</span>
    </h2>
    <p>Top-level identifiers and lifecycle state. The automation engine uses these fields to route issues, update labels, and build the public course listing.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Values / Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>kebab-case, globally unique URL slug, e.g. <code>git-mastery</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>string</td><td>semver — bump on every meaningful change, e.g. <code>"1.0.0"</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>schema_version</code></td><td>string</td><td>Always <code>"3.0"</code> — do not change</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>status</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>draft</code> · <code>review</code> · <code>published</code> · <code>archived</code> · <code>deprecated</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>visibility</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>public</code> · <code>unlisted</code> · <code>private</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>created_at</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 8601 date, e.g. <code>"2025-01-15"</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>updated_at</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 8601 — update every time you change the file</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>published_at</code></td><td>string | null</td><td>Set by automation on publish; start as <code>null</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>language</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 639-1 code, e.g. <code>en</code>, <code>hi</code>, <code>ta</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>locale</code></td><td>string</td><td>Optional. e.g. <code>en-US</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>slug_aliases</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>Optional. Old slugs that redirect to this course</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>solutions_file</code></td><td>string</td><td>Path to companion solutions.yaml — used by grader at runtime</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>metadata:
  id: git-mastery
  version: "1.0.0"
  schema_version: "3.0"
  status: draft
  visibility: public
  created_at: "2025-01-15"
  updated_at: "2025-01-15"
  published_at: null
  language: en
  solutions_file: solutions.yaml</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 2: IDENTITY -->
  <section id="s2-identity" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§2 — Identity</h2>
    <p>What students see on the course listing and player. The <code>description.full</code> field supports GitHub Flavored Markdown. Course artwork is generated automatically from <code>classification.category</code>, so authors do not need banners, thumbnails, OG images, or badge artwork.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>title</code></td><td>string</td><td>Course title, max ~60 chars for display</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>tagline</code></td><td>string</td><td>One-sentence hook, ~100 chars</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>description.short</code></td><td>string</td><td>Plain text, 1–2 sentences, used in cards and meta tags</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>description.full</code></td><td>markdown</td><td>Full course description — shown in player. GFM supported.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cover.color_primary</code></td><td>hex</td><td>Optional course accent color, e.g. <code>#f59e0b</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>cover.color_secondary</code></td><td>hex</td><td>Optional secondary accent color</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>classification.category</code></td><td>track slug</td><td>Drives the generated abstract artwork used by cards and course heroes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 3: CLASSIFICATION ══ -->
  <section id="s3-classify" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§3 — Classification</h2>
    <p>Drives the track filter, search, and prerequisite graph on the courses page.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>category</code></td><td>string</td><td>Must be one of the 12 valid track slugs (see below)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>subcategory</code></td><td>string</td><td>Free-form sub-topic, e.g. <code>version-control</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>tags</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>3–8 lowercase tags for search</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>topics</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>More specific concepts covered</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>level</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>beginner</code> · <code>intermediate</code> · <code>advanced</code> · <code>mixed</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>target_audience</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>Who this course is for</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>skills_gained</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>Specific skills students leave with — shown in player sidebar</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Valid <code>category</code> track slugs:</strong></p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code># 12 valid track slugs for classification.category:
foundations   # Git, DS&amp;A, algorithms, discrete math, theory
languages     # C, C++, Rust, Python, Java, Haskell, SQL, ...
web           # HTML, CSS, JS/TS, React, Vue, iOS, Android, ...
backend       # REST APIs, SQL, NoSQL, microservices, GraphQL
systems       # OS, compilers, Docker, Kubernetes, CI/CD, cloud
networks      # TCP/IP, HTTP/3, TLS, BGP, WebRTC, ...
data          # ETL, ML, deep learning, LLMs, MLOps, Spark
security      # OWASP, crypto, pentesting, zero-knowledge
architecture  # system design, patterns, DDD, TDD, CQRS
creative      # graphics, shaders, game engines, procedural gen
emerging      # quantum, neuromorphic, blockchain, formal verification
applied       # bioinformatics, robotics, HPC, scientific computing</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 4: EFFORT ══ -->
  <section id="s4-effort" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§4 — Effort</h2>
    <p>Time estimates shown to students on the course card and player header. Be realistic — overpromising undermines trust.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>video_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>Total video content hours (decimals allowed)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>reading_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>Estimated reading time across all lessons</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>exercise_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>Hands-on exercises and assignments</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>total_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>Sum of the three above — used for the duration display</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>pace</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>self-paced</code> · <code>scheduled</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>weekly_commitment_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>Recommended hours per week</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>completion_weeks</code></td><td>number</td><td>Estimated weeks at the recommended pace</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 5: PEOPLE ══ -->
  <section id="s5-people" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§5 — People</h2>
    <p>The <code>curator</code> is the primary author who maintains the course. <code>contributors</code> and <code>reviewers</code> are optional but credited on the site and in the certificate.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>people:
  curator:
    name: "Jane Smith"
    github: janesmith
    role: "Course Author"
    bio: "Senior engineer specializing in distributed systems."
    avatar: null                  # null = use GitHub avatar

  contributors:
    - name: "Alex Kumar"
      github: alexkumar
      role: reviewer
      contributions: ["exercises", "solutions review"]

  reviewers:
    - name: "Maria Garcia"
      github: mariagarcia
      expertise: "security"</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 6: CREDITS ══ -->
  <section id="s6-credits" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§6 — Credits</h2>
    <p>Every external resource (video, article, repo, dataset, book) used in the curriculum must have a credit entry. Lessons reference credits by their <code>id</code> field via <code>credit_id</code>.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>string</td><td>e.g. <code>src-01</code> — referenced by lessons via <code>credit_id: src-01</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>type</code></td><td>enum</td><td><code>video</code> · <code>repo</code> · <code>article</code> · <code>book</code> · <code>tool</code> · <code>dataset</code> · <code>course</code> · <code>podcast</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>title</code></td><td>string</td><td>Full title of the resource</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>author</code></td><td>string</td><td>Creator or author name</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>organization</code></td><td>string?</td><td>Optional. Company, university, or channel</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>url</code></td><td>string</td><td>Canonical URL</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>license</code></td><td>string</td><td>e.g. <code>CC BY 4.0</code>, <code>MIT</code>, <code>YouTube Standard</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>license_url</code></td><td>string?</td><td>Link to license text</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>accessed_at</code></td><td>string</td><td>ISO 8601 date you last verified the URL</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>notes</code></td><td>string?</td><td>Any curation notes</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>archived_url</code></td><td>string?</td><td>Archive.org or Wayback link for link-rot protection</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>


