  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 9: CURRICULUM ══ -->
  <section id="s9-curriculum" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§9 — Curriculum</h2>
    <p>The content hierarchy is: <strong>course → chapter → section (optional) → subsection (optional) → lesson</strong>. Lessons are the leaf nodes — one learning unit each.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>curriculum:
  chapters:
    - id: ch-01
      title: "Getting Started with Git"
      description: "Install Git, initialise a repo, make your first commit."
      duration_minutes: 90
      free_preview: false
      outcomes:
        - "Initialise a Git repository"
        - "Stage and commit changes"

      # Direct lessons (no sections needed for simple chapters):
      lessons:
        - id: ch-01-l-01
          title: "What is Version Control?"
          type: video
          duration_minutes: 12
          free_preview: true
          description: "Overview of why version control exists and what problem Git solves."
          content:
            video:
              url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID"
              source: youtube
              channel: "Fireship"
              credit_id: src-01        # references credits[].id
              subtitles_available: true
              timestamps:
                - label: "Intro"
                  time: "0:00"
                - label: "Why version control?"
                  time: "0:45"
                - label: "Git vs SVN"
                  time: "2:10"
            text:
              format: markdown
              body: |
                ## Curator Notes
                This video gives an excellent 12-minute overview.
                Pay special attention to the **object model** at 6:30 —
                it's the foundation of everything else in this course.
            links:
              - label: "Git official documentation"
                url: "https://git-scm.com/doc"
                type: documentation
                required: true

      # Sections (optional grouping within a chapter):
      sections:
        - id: ch-01-s-01
          title: "Installation &amp; Setup"
          lessons:
            - id: ch-01-s-01-l-01
              title: "Installing Git"
              type: reading
              duration_minutes: 8
              content:
                reading:
                  url: "https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git"
                  source: "Pro Git (Chacon &amp; Straub)"
                  credit_id: src-02
                  estimated_minutes: 8
                  sections_to_read: ["Installing on Linux", "Installing on macOS"]
                text:
                  format: markdown
                  body: |
                    Read the installation section for your OS.
                    After installing, run `git --version` to verify.

      chapter_test_id: ctest-ch-01      # must match a chapter_tests[].id below
      chapter_assignment_id: cassign-ch-01   # optional</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ LESSON TYPE REFERENCE ══ -->
  <section id="lesson-types" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Lesson Types — Full Reference</h2>
    <p>Every lesson has a <code>type</code> field. The type determines what fields appear under <code>content:</code> and how the course player renders it.</p>

    <div class="lesson-type-grid">

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">▶</span><span class="lt-card__name">video</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Curated video with timestamps and curator notes. YouTube (privacy-enhanced embed) and Vimeo supported automatically.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>video.url</code> — original link [REQUIRED]</div>
          <div><code>video.embed_url</code> — override auto-derived iframe src [optional]</div>
          <div><code>video.source</code> — "youtube" | "vimeo" | etc.</div>
          <div><code>video.channel</code> — channel/creator name</div>
          <div><code>video.credit_id</code> — links to credits[].id</div>
          <div><code>video.subtitles_available</code> — true/false</div>
          <div><code>video.timestamps[]</code> — &#123;label, time&#125; pairs</div>
          <div><code>text.body</code> — curator notes (markdown)</div>
          <div><code>links[]</code> — related resources</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">📖</span><span class="lt-card__name">reading</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Link to an article, doc page, or book chapter. The player shows a "Read on source" button with curator notes alongside.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>reading.url</code> — canonical URL [REQUIRED]</div>
          <div><code>reading.source</code> — publication name</div>
          <div><code>reading.credit_id</code> — links to credits[].id</div>
          <div><code>reading.estimated_minutes</code> — reading time</div>
          <div><code>reading.sections_to_read[]</code> — which sections</div>
          <div><code>reading.sections_to_skip[]</code> — sections to skip</div>
          <div><code>text.body</code> — curator notes (markdown)</div>
          <div><code>supplemental[]</code> — extra reading</div>
          <div><code>links[]</code> — related resources</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">💻</span><span class="lt-card__name">code</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Annotated code walkthrough. Supports multiple code blocks per lesson, each with syntax highlighting, explanation, and expected output.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>text.body</code> — intro/context (markdown)</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].id</code> — unique block id</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].title</code> — display name</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].language</code> — e.g. python, js, bash</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].snippet</code> — the code [REQUIRED]</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].explanation</code> — inline prose</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].expected_output</code> — output to show</div>
          <div><code>code_blocks[].runnable</code> — true/false hint</div>
          <div><code>links[]</code> — related resources</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">🛠</span><span class="lt-card__name">exercise</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Hands-on task. Student clones a starter repo, implements a solution, and submits. Hints reveal progressively.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>text.body</code> — task instructions (markdown)</div>
          <div><code>exercise.starter_repo</code> — GitHub URL [REQUIRED]</div>
          <div><code>exercise.solution_repo</code> — private reference</div>
          <div><code>exercise.branch</code> — branch name</div>
          <div><code>exercise.test_command</code> — e.g. "npm test"</div>
          <div><code>exercise.submission_type</code> — github_url | file_upload | inline</div>
          <div><code>hints[].level</code> — 1, 2, 3 (progressive)</div>
          <div><code>hints[].text</code> — hint content</div>
          <div><code>files[]</code> — assets provided</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">📋</span><span class="lt-card__name">reference</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Cheatsheet, table, or quick-reference card. Pure curator-authored content with supporting files and links.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>text.body</code> — reference content (markdown)</div>
          <div><code>files[]</code> — downloadable PDFs, images</div>
          <div><code>links[]</code> — external references</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">📝</span><span class="lt-card__name">quiz</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Ungraded formative check with instant feedback. Questions live inside the lesson — NOT in chapter_tests (which are graded).</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>questions[].id</code></div>
          <div><code>questions[].type</code> — mcq | truefalse | short</div>
          <div><code>questions[].question</code></div>
          <div><code>questions[].options[]</code> — for mcq</div>
          <div><code>questions[].answer</code> — shown after attempt</div>
          <div><code>questions[].explanation</code></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">💬</span><span class="lt-card__name">discussion</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Open-ended prompt for GitHub Discussions. Creates a pinned discussion thread when the chapter is unlocked.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div><code>text.body</code> — the discussion prompt (markdown)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lt-card">
        <div class="lt-card__head"><span class="lt-card__icon">🚀</span><span class="lt-card__name">project</span></div>
        <div class="lt-card__desc">Multi-lesson deliverable within a chapter. Used for mini-projects that span several lesson nodes before a submission.</div>
        <div class="lt-card__fields">
          <div>Same fields as <code>exercise</code></div>
          <div>Spans multiple lessons — mark each phase as a project lesson</div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 10: CHAPTER TESTS ══ -->
  <section id="s10-tests" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§10 — Chapter Tests</h2>
    <p>A top-level array of graded assessments. Each chapter references one test via <code>chapter_test_id</code>. Tests contain no answers — answers live exclusively in <code>solutions.yaml</code>.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>chapter_tests:
  - id: ctest-ch-01
    title: "Chapter 1 Test: Git Foundations"
    attached_to: ch-01
    gates_next_chapter: true      # student can't proceed until passing
    passing_score: 70             # percent 0–100
    max_attempts: 3
    time_limit_minutes: 30
    randomize_questions: true
    randomize_options: true
    show_answers_after: passed    # passed | attempted | never

    sections:
      - id: ctest-ch-01-s-01
        title: "Core Concepts"
        weight: 60                # percent of total test score
        questions:
          - id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-01
            type: mcq
            points: 2
            difficulty: easy
            topic: "git-objects"
            question: "Which Git object stores a directory listing?"
            options:
              - "blob"
              - "tree"
              - "commit"
              - "tag"
            # Answer is in solutions.yaml — NOT here

          - id: ctest-ch-01-s-01-q-02
            type: truefalse
            points: 1
            difficulty: easy
            question: "The working tree and the staging area (index) are the same thing."
            # Answer: false — in solutions.yaml

      - id: ctest-ch-01-s-02
        title: "Applied Git"
        weight: 40
        questions:
          - id: ctest-ch-01-s-02-q-01
            type: code_output
            points: 3
            difficulty: medium
            question: "What does this command output?"
            code:
              language: bash
              snippet: |
                git log --oneline -3
            options:
              - "The last 3 commit hashes only"
              - "The last 3 commits with abbreviated hash and subject line"
              - "All commits by 3 authors"
              - "An error — -3 is not a valid flag"</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 11: CH ASSIGNMENTS ══ -->
  <section id="s11-assign" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§11 — Chapter Assignments</h2>
    <p>Optional hands-on projects attached to chapters. Unlike tests, assignments require human review or run through the Docker sandbox grader.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>chapter_assignments:
  - id: cassign-ch-01
    title: "Build Your First Repository"
    attached_to: ch-01
    required_for_progress: false
    submission_type: github_url
    due_after_enrollment_days: 7
    max_resubmissions: 2
    content:
      text:
        format: markdown
        body: |
          ## Task
          Create a public GitHub repository with at least 5 meaningful commits.
          The commit history should tell a coherent story of building something small.
      links:
        - label: "Example repository"
          url: "https://github.com/..."
          type: repo
    rubric:
      - criterion: "Minimum 5 commits with descriptive messages"
        points: 10
      - criterion: "Uses feature branches with clear names"
        points: 5
      - criterion: "Includes a README with project purpose"
        points: 5
    total_points: 20
    passing_score: 70
    review:
      type: maintainer
      sla_days: 3
      feedback_required: true</code>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 12: FINAL TEST ═══ -->
  <section id="s12-final-test" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§12 — Final Test</h2>
    <p>Comprehensive exam covering the entire course. Required for certificate generation when <code>required_for_certificate: true</code>. Structure mirrors chapter tests — sections of questions, no answers embedded here.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
