  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════ SECTION 14: CERTIFICATE ══ -->
  <section id="s14-cert" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">§14 — Certificate</h2>
    <p>When all requirements are met, the automation issues a <strong>GPG-signed SVG certificate</strong> with embedded <strong>Open Badges 3.0 metadata</strong> as a GitHub Release — verifiable by anyone with the project's public GPG key.</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>certificate:
  enabled: true
  title: "Git Mastery Certificate"
  subtitle: "Awarded for demonstrating professional Git proficiency"
  requirements:
    - type: final_test
      id: final-test
      min_score: 75
    - type: final_assignment
      id: final-assignment
      min_score: 70
    # type: chapter_test + id + min_score also valid
  template: default                 # default | minimal | dark
  custom_template: null             # path to custom SVG template (optional)</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--tip">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">✅</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">The certificate SVG is published as a GitHub Release asset and linked from the student's enrollment issue. Anyone can verify it using <code>gpg --verify certificate.svg</code> with the project's public key.</div>
    </div>
  </section>


